HEADWORD: Forgather
<hw>For*gath"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To convene; to
gossip; to meet accidentally.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within that circle he <qex>forgathered</qex> with many a fool.</q>
<rj><qau>Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forgave</ent>⟦br⟧
